subSubSection.paragraph:
Main receptacle axis not continuing into a lateral branch above the perithecium. Appendages 
types
“a” and “b” inseparable, very abundant, deeply darkened. Perithecium broadly oval, very inflated, up to 60 µm in width, showing a ± conspicuous preapical darkened ring. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1896
; 
Majewski 1994b
; 
De Kesel 2002
]
